From: SDDC_FX3 maintainers
Subject: [PATCH] rx888: send STARTADC before STARTFX3 for SDDC firmware compatibility

ka9q-radio programs the Si5351 ADC clock chip directly via raw
I2CWFX3 writes (rx888.c:331, rx888.c:340) and intentionally never
calls STARTADC.  This is a deliberate design choice that works
against stock RX888 firmware where STARTADC does only Si5351 setup.

SDDC firmware (https://github.com/ringof/ExtIO_sddc) tracks
ADC-clock readiness via a separate global flag `glAdcClockEnabled`
(SDDC_FX3/driver/Si5351.c:55), which is set CyTrue *only* inside
`si5351aSetFrequencyA(freq>0)` (SDDC_FX3/driver/Si5351.c:250),
which is called *only* from the STARTADC handler
(SDDC_FX3/USBHandler.c:219).  The STARTFX3 handler then runs
`GpifPreflightCheck()` (SDDC_FX3/StartStopApplication.c:99) before
starting the GPIF state machine:

    if (!si5351_clk0_enabled())  return CyFalse;  // glAdcClockEnabled
    if (!si5351_pll_locked())    return CyFalse;

`si5351_clk0_enabled()` returns the bare flag
(SDDC_FX3/driver/Si5351.c:174) — it does not query the chip — so
even though ka9q has correctly programmed Si5351 via I2C and the
PLL is physically locked, the flag remains CyFalse.  STARTFX3 stalls
EP0 (SDDC_FX3/USBHandler.c:333), the GPIF state machine never
starts, no bulk data flows, and radiod times out:

    rx888 running
    No rx888 data for 5 seconds, quitting

Comparison: rx888_stream (the SDDC firmware test harness) sends
STARTADC immediately before STARTFX3 (rx888_stream.c:1185 / 1193),
which is what SDDC requires.

Fix: send STARTADC with the configured sample rate just before
STARTFX3 in `rx888_start_rx()`.  Effects:

  - Reprograms Si5351 to the same frequency ka9q already programmed
    via I2C — same register sequence, harmless duplicate write.
  - Sets glAdcClockEnabled = CyTrue inside the firmware.
  - Firmware blocks for up to 100 ms polling PLL lock; PLL is
    already locked so this returns immediately.
  - Subsequent STARTFX3 preflight passes; GPIF starts; samples flow.

The 5 ms usleep after STARTADC matches the existing inter-command
spacing pattern in rx888_start_rx and gives the firmware's I2C
transactions a brief settle time, even though STARTADC's 100 ms
PLL-lock poll already host-blocks the EP0 status phase.

Pinned against ka9q-radio commit f78cff9cc8c7fa33ea49aac9176d9263c535a332.
---
 src/rx888.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/rx888.c b/src/rx888.c
index 0000000..0000000 100644
--- a/src/rx888.c
+++ b/src/rx888.c
@@ -998,6 +998,8 @@
   }

   usleep(5000);
+  command_send(sdr->dev_handle,STARTADC,sdr->frontend->samprate);
+  usleep(5000);
   command_send(sdr->dev_handle,STARTFX3,0);
   usleep(5000);
   command_send(sdr->dev_handle,TUNERSTDBY,0);

